      "fun_fact": "Hopper loved this area of Cape Cod so much that he later built his home there.",
      "digital_description": null,
      "wall_description": "A deeply reserved individual and intensely independent artist, Hopper sought to capture, in his words, \"the sad desolation\" of America. His works—including this Cape Cod landscape of a lone house next to a railroad track amid a backdrop of rolling hills—typically inject mundane scenes with a profound sense of solitude. The painter Charles Burchfield once described Hopper’s art as \"silent poetry.\"",
