          "citations": [
            
          ],
          "footnotes": [
            "The circumstances surrounding Leupp's acquisition of this painting, as well as its return to Mrs. Lee, his mother-in-law, after his death are unclear. Leupp,a founder of The Century Association, greatly admired the painting; Mount recalled that in the spring of 1847 Leupp \"stood a long time looking at it until I began to think I had made a failure and observed to him, ‘If you think this picture will not suit Mrs. Lee, I will paint her another with pleasure.’ ‘Why man,’ he said, ‘I only wish the picture belonged to me.’” By at least 1856, the painting did go to Leupp; in that year <em>The Crayon</em> listed it as part of his collection."
          ],
