      "fun_fact": "Krasner repurposed this large canvas when she painted over an earlier composition that dissatisfied her.",
      "digital_description": "After the death of her husband Jackson Pollock, Krasner took over his studio located in a barn on their property. With this expansion of studio space, she began creating large-scale paintings like Celebration,using expansive gestures to express her feelings on canvas.",
      "wall_description": "Krasner once proclaimed, \"I swing from the lyric to the dramatic,\"and her mature style consists of highly gestural brushwork that can be alternately blissful and ferocious within the same composition. Celebration embodies this approach particularly well, combining gentler organic shapes with frenzied thrusts, whiplashes, and spatters of paint. Its expansive scale fills the visual field of observers who stand a customary distance from it, providing an uncanny experience of envelopment.",
